- Get him back here.
- Stop!

12
00:01:26,670 --> 00:01:27,670
Don't run.

13
00:01:27,921 --> 00:01:28,921
Let go of me.

14
00:01:29,131 --> 00:01:30,423
- Let go of me.
- Go back.

15
00:01:30,591 --> 00:01:31,424
Go back!

16
00:01:32,301 --> 00:01:34,468
- Let go of me.
- Go back.

17
00:01:35,345 --> 00:01:36,345
Let me go.

18
00:01:36,513 --> 00:01:38,097
Don't you ever go near her tent again.

19
00:01:39,391 --> 00:01:42,685
- I told you she will jinx you.
- Get back.

20
00:01:42,853 --> 00:01:44,687
Let me go, let me go.

21
00:04:45,577 --> 00:04:46,577
Witch.

22
00:04:46,745 --> 00:04:47,953
- Witch.
- Witch.

23
00:04:48,747 --> 00:04:49,997
- Witch.
- Witch.

24
00:04:51,416 --> 00:04:52,416
Witch.

25
00:04:59,341 --> 00:05:00,341
Witch.

26
00:05:02,219 --> 00:05:05,513
The witch is here. Quickly! Run!

27
00:05:06,723 --> 00:05:08,265
I told you to stay away from that tent.

28
00:05:08,433 --> 00:05:09,975
Why wouldn't you listen to me?

29
00:05:10,477 --> 00:05:12,186
Go home now!

30
00:05:12,479 --> 00:05:13,813
Orthe devil will come.

31
00:05:24,783 --> 00:05:25,783
Yongcuo.

32
00:05:30,413 --> 00:05:31,497
Yongcuo.

33
00:05:33,667 --> 00:05:34,750
You are so beautiful.

34
00:05:46,972 --> 00:05:47,763
Yongcuo.

35
00:05:47,973 --> 00:05:50,182
Here, take the meat.

36
00:05:51,309 --> 00:05:53,060
Eat, Yongcuo.

37
00:05:53,937 --> 00:05:54,937
And this.

38
00:05:56,606 --> 00:06:00,067
Yongcuo, and this lamb too.

39
00:06:04,906 --> 00:06:09,159
Yongcuo.
Can I be the child's father?

40
00:06:09,452 --> 00:06:10,828
Can I, Yongcuo?

41
00:06:15,709 --> 00:06:17,751
Yongcuo, don't you want it?

42
00:06:18,712 --> 00:06:19,712
- Luosang!
- Here you go.

43
00:06:20,046 --> 00:06:21,797
- Get back here.
- Take it.

44
00:06:22,048 --> 00:06:24,925
You can't go there.
You should watch out that witch.

45
00:06:48,450 --> 00:06:49,950
Who's there?

46
00:06:52,078 --> 00:06:53,078
Hello?

47
00:08:55,118 --> 00:08:57,703
I saw the devil by the lake.

48
00:08:59,039 --> 00:09:00,039
Over there.

49
00:09:02,917 --> 00:09:04,209
Here comes Grandpa Danzeng.

50
00:09:08,465 --> 00:09:10,799
Devil! He must be the Devil!

51
00:09:11,342 --> 00:09:14,094
He is no devil. He's a foreigner.

52
00:09:14,345 --> 00:09:16,513
I saw them once in India
when I was young.

53
00:09:23,229 --> 00:09:24,688
He's still alive.

54
00:09:26,024 --> 00:09:26,815
The British.

55
00:09:26,983 --> 00:09:29,902
The damn British are here again.

56
00:09:30,236 --> 00:09:34,073
What should we do?
Where can we hide him?

57
00:09:37,035 --> 00:09:38,452
This is the only way out.

58
00:10:35,677 --> 00:10:36,677
Grandpa Danzeng.

59
00:10:37,095 --> 00:10:38,428
He is either the devil...

60
00:10:38,805 --> 00:10:40,764
...or coming out of the snow,

61
00:10:40,932 --> 00:10:42,349
or falling from the sky.

62
00:10:42,684 --> 00:10:44,601
Ask him yourself when he's awake.

63
00:10:51,943 --> 00:10:54,403
Come here Yongcuo, quickly!

64
00:11:00,827 --> 00:11:03,245
Here, give me your hand.

65
00:11:03,788 --> 00:11:07,040
Don't go. You gotta help me here.

66
00:11:07,625 --> 00:11:09,960
I only have one pair of hands.

67
00:11:13,006 --> 00:11:14,548
Yes that's it.

68
00:11:14,883 --> 00:11:17,551
Rub gently just like
the way you spin the Prayer Wheel.

69
00:11:17,927 --> 00:11:21,388
Do it until his skin gets
as hot as fresh cow muck.

70
00:12:20,740 --> 00:12:22,407
Oh, my head hurts like hell.

71
00:12:23,117 --> 00:12:25,202
You owe me three sheep.

72
00:12:28,039 --> 00:12:29,039
Two.

73
00:13:15,837 --> 00:13:18,213
We are 26 degrees off
from our original course.

74
00:13:18,673 --> 00:13:20,465
I am trying to recalibrate
the navigation system.

75
00:13:20,717 --> 00:13:22,342
It's not responding!

76
00:13:25,221 --> 00:13:26,555
We are falling fast!

77
00:13:29,392 --> 00:13:32,352
Now! Now! Now!

78
00:13:52,332 --> 00:13:54,041
Huang, help me!
I can't move this one.

79
00:14:04,260 --> 00:14:05,260
Robert.

80
00:14:05,428 --> 00:14:06,970
Get a hold of yourself.
We are going to be joining him very soon.

81
00:14:07,347 --> 00:14:13,018
Grab a parachute
and jump out of the plane.

82
00:14:14,312 --> 00:14:15,645
This is yours.

83
00:14:17,065 --> 00:14:19,399
Goodbye, buddy. Good luck!

84
00:14:19,650 --> 00:14:21,276
What? You...

85
00:14:21,569 --> 00:14:25,489
Ouraltitude is already
too low to parachute. Jump!

86
00:14:25,656 --> 00:14:26,740
Don't be stupid, Jack.

87
00:14:26,949 --> 00:14:32,454
One... Two... Three.

88
00:14:38,336 --> 00:14:39,544
Don't touch my stuff.

89
00:14:43,549 --> 00:14:44,549
Where am I?

90
00:14:44,717 --> 00:14:46,468
You still owe me two sheep.

91
00:15:03,486 --> 00:15:07,030
This man's eyes
have seen too much filth.

92
00:15:07,198 --> 00:15:08,990
They could be easily
damaged by the snow.

93
00:15:09,492 --> 00:15:12,285
We can treat his eyes using your breast
milkwith the medicine I have blessed.

94
00:15:12,537 --> 00:15:13,954
Then he could be cured.

95
00:15:14,163 --> 00:15:15,956
My breast milk is for my child.

96
00:15:18,584 --> 00:15:23,380
Here's the medicine; give me two sheep.

97
00:15:24,590 --> 00:15:27,467
Two! You can't afford it, can you?

98
00:15:27,802 --> 00:15:29,344
Poor Yongcuo.

99
00:17:06,859 --> 00:17:08,151
What are you doing?

100
00:17:09,278 --> 00:17:10,278
What are you doing?

101
00:18:15,344 --> 00:18:16,720
Excuse me, sir.

102
00:18:17,013 --> 00:18:18,847
You don't have any identification,

103
00:18:19,015 --> 00:18:21,516
so this is an illegal immigration.

104
00:18:21,809 --> 00:18:22,767
And who are you, sir?

105
00:18:23,019 --> 00:18:25,562
I am a special officer,
SuoLang Wangdui.

106
00:18:26,522 --> 00:18:28,356
This is Major Sun.

107
00:18:28,691 --> 00:18:31,776
But, butwe can't
stay in a place like this.

108
00:18:31,944 --> 00:18:35,071
We just want to go home,
we want to go home to our home countries.

109
00:18:35,448 --> 00:18:38,450
Sorry. Here is not neutral in the war.

110
00:18:38,868 --> 00:18:40,285
You are in the land of China.

111
00:18:41,120 --> 00:18:44,372
A country that's hostile
against your countries.

112
00:18:46,584 --> 00:18:47,917
Where are you sending us?

113
00:18:48,169 --> 00:18:51,171
Unfortunately you have to go
back to where you came from.

114
00:18:52,548 --> 00:18:54,132
No, no! Please don't send us back.

115
00:18:54,300 --> 00:18:58,637
You can't send us back.

116
00:18:58,888 --> 00:19:02,265
Please, sir. I beg you.
It will be inhuman.

117
00:19:02,558 --> 00:19:05,435
I'd rather die, please,
I can't go back there.

118
00:19:05,603 --> 00:19:10,231
I can't go back there.

119
00:19:12,735 --> 00:19:13,902
Good job.

120
00:19:14,195 --> 00:19:15,945
- Return to your own tribes.
- Yes, sir.

121
00:19:38,219 --> 00:19:39,302
Jiangcuo.

122
00:19:40,596 --> 00:19:41,596
Yangjin.

123
00:19:44,892 --> 00:19:48,269
You are great.
Everyone is praising your bravery...

124
00:19:48,562 --> 00:19:49,688
...for capturing so many
red haired devils this time.

125
00:19:51,065 --> 00:19:52,732
Those red haired
devils aren't real devils.

126
00:19:53,109 --> 00:19:55,443
They just wanted to go home
but ended up in the wrong place.

127
00:19:59,740 --> 00:20:00,949
Does it still hurt?

128
00:20:05,579 --> 00:20:07,080
In a few days,

129
00:20:07,790 --> 00:20:10,500
I will be returning
to the tribe with Madam.

130
00:20:11,460 --> 00:20:14,504
Be sure to drop by and visit me,
Jiangcuo.

131
00:20:18,092 --> 00:20:19,092
Yangjin.

132
00:20:20,136 --> 00:20:26,433
The Chief wouldn't let me see you
when I go back.

133
00:20:27,351 --> 00:20:30,103
I would be locked up in a hut to tan hides.

134
00:20:31,772 --> 00:20:37,152
I will be satisfied if I could just
get a glimpse of you from afar.

135
00:20:39,488 --> 00:20:40,488
Yangjin.

136
00:21:55,606 --> 00:21:59,317
I can see! I can see!

137
00:22:02,613 --> 00:22:04,322
I can see!

138
00:22:19,004 --> 00:22:23,007
So this is you. You are very beautiful.

139
00:22:24,885 --> 00:22:28,304
Where'd your beard go?

140
00:22:28,514 --> 00:22:30,390
Yeah. I can see.

141
00:22:30,558 --> 00:22:31,474
You can see now?

142
00:22:31,725 --> 00:22:32,725
I can see.

143
00:22:42,486 --> 00:22:45,905
Sorry for the trouble.

144
00:22:49,493 --> 00:22:52,954
Thank you for curing my eyes.

145
00:22:56,542 --> 00:23:00,044
Can I help you? I can help you.

146
00:23:20,816 --> 00:23:22,150
- Witch.
- Witch.

147
00:23:22,401 --> 00:23:28,573
Red haired devil.

148
00:23:29,450 --> 00:23:31,284
- Witch.
- Witch.

149
00:23:31,535 --> 00:23:32,952
- What's happening?
- Get inside.

150
00:23:33,829 --> 00:23:34,954
What are they doing here?

151
00:23:38,876 --> 00:23:40,460
The witch brought
the red haired devil here.

152
00:23:40,753 --> 00:23:42,420
Move! Move!

153
00:23:46,550 --> 00:23:48,134
- Away from her.
- Away from her.

154
00:24:04,318 --> 00:24:07,820
Thank you forsaving me.

155
00:24:11,575 --> 00:24:14,035
I'm very honored to be here with you.

156
00:24:19,333 --> 00:24:20,333
I'm an American.

157
00:24:22,419 --> 00:24:24,253
I need to get to Lhasa.

158
00:24:27,675 --> 00:24:28,675
Lhasa?

159
00:24:31,136 --> 00:24:32,136
Lhasa.

160
00:24:32,429 --> 00:24:33,805
He wants to go to Lhasa?

161
00:24:33,973 --> 00:24:35,932
Chief, he wants to go to Lhasa.

162
00:24:36,100 --> 00:24:37,308
This can't be done.

163
00:24:38,227 --> 00:24:39,310
You want to go to Lhasa?

164
00:24:41,438 --> 00:24:42,438
Lhasa.

165
00:24:43,607 --> 00:24:45,942
Can you? you can take me to Lhasa?

166
00:24:57,496 --> 00:25:03,209
This is the order issued by the Dalai Lama
under the authority of the Qing Emperor...

167
00:25:03,377 --> 00:25:06,587
...that forbids foreigners from
trespassing into the sacred Tibet.

168
00:25:09,383 --> 00:25:10,800
Forty years ago,

169
00:25:12,302 --> 00:25:13,636
you British raided Tibet,

170
00:25:13,846 --> 00:25:15,680
murdered countless our people,

171
00:25:16,890 --> 00:25:19,142
and even plundered the most
sacred treasures of our religion.

172
00:25:19,560 --> 00:25:22,228
You should not even be here.
Go! Leave now!

173
00:25:30,654 --> 00:25:32,739
This is a waste oftime.

174
00:26:34,510 --> 00:26:38,471
- You can't leave now. You can't go.
- I have to go.

175
00:26:38,806 --> 00:26:40,681
- The snow will seal the mountain off soon.
- I am a military officer.

176
00:26:40,849 --> 00:26:43,601
- You can't go. You can't.
- I can't stay here. I can't stay here.

177
00:26:44,770 --> 00:26:45,812
Thank you.

178
00:26:51,193 --> 00:26:54,153
Chief, look!
The red haired devil is leaving.

179
00:26:57,074 --> 00:27:00,660
Do you think he could make it
crossing the snow mountain?

180
00:27:01,620 --> 00:27:05,957
No one can cross
that mountain in this season.

181
00:27:08,836 --> 00:27:10,169
Lord Constable,

182
00:27:10,379 --> 00:27:12,713
the shepherd reported that
a red haired devil murdered a woman.

183
00:27:12,881 --> 00:27:13,881
Where did this happen?

184
00:27:14,383 --> 00:27:16,551
The tribe of Kaluo.

185
00:27:19,763 --> 00:27:21,013
Have you heard of it?

186
00:27:21,181 --> 00:27:22,723
A red haired devil killed one ofus.

187
00:27:23,517 --> 00:27:27,061
So I've heared. The government's
people are hunting him down.

188
00:27:28,897 --> 00:27:31,566
Our tribe would rather
pay more taxes as a penalty...

189
00:27:31,733 --> 00:27:34,026
...than having more people drafted
to serve the government.

190
00:27:35,404 --> 00:27:36,571
- Master.
- Master.

191
00:27:39,491 --> 00:27:41,117
What's the name of your slave again?

192
00:27:50,460 --> 00:27:51,919
Is she your woman?

193
00:27:53,714 --> 00:27:58,050
I'm waiting for the Chief's
permission to marry her.

194
00:28:02,764 --> 00:28:05,057
Find me the foreign murderer,

195
00:28:05,767 --> 00:28:07,268
then you will redeem your freedom,

196
00:28:07,811 --> 00:28:09,270
and marry that woman.

197
00:28:12,733 --> 00:28:18,779
Lord Constable,
thank you so much. Thank you.

198
00:28:22,659 --> 00:28:23,743
You could get up now.

199
00:28:27,623 --> 00:28:28,623
Yes.

200
00:28:30,709 --> 00:28:31,834
Lord Constable,

201
00:28:32,461 --> 00:28:33,878
I vow to bring him back...

202
00:28:34,379 --> 00:28:36,005
...even if it will cost my life.

203
00:28:37,174 --> 00:28:38,174
Go.

204
00:28:48,936 --> 00:28:49,936
Let's go.

205
00:29:51,581 --> 00:29:53,708
Grandpa Danzeng,
please save him. Please.

206
00:29:54,584 --> 00:29:56,085
What's wrong? Let me see.

207
00:30:03,719 --> 00:30:10,224
Yongcuo, your child's gone.
He didn't like it here.

208
00:32:48,341 --> 00:32:50,551
This place is too poor.

209
00:32:51,219 --> 00:32:53,512
There's no temple, no Lamas.

210
00:32:54,222 --> 00:32:58,392
Even Buddha drifting pass here
would refuse to stay.

211
00:32:59,102 --> 00:33:05,065
The Buddha will bless you
as long as you believe in Him.

212
00:33:06,151 --> 00:33:08,027
Will the Buddha bless my child too?

213
00:33:08,987 --> 00:33:11,989
Buddha bless all.

214
00:33:49,402 --> 00:33:52,238
- The bandits are here. Run!
- The bandits are here.

215
00:34:00,830 --> 00:34:03,707
Don't be afraid.
The government sent us here.

216
00:34:05,835 --> 00:34:07,294
Hey! Get back here.

217
00:34:09,339 --> 00:34:13,175
Please eat.
The journey must have been exhausting.

218
00:34:13,677 --> 00:34:15,094
It must have been exhausting.

219
00:34:26,815 --> 00:34:27,815
Jiangcuo.

220
00:34:28,233 --> 00:34:31,527
Yangjin, what brought you here?
Let's go.

221
00:34:34,656 --> 00:34:38,242
You guys moved as fast as the wind.

222
00:34:38,535 --> 00:34:40,077
It took me days to catch you up.

223
00:34:49,379 --> 00:34:50,379
Yangjin,

224
00:34:51,423 --> 00:34:53,215
when I get the red haired devil this time,

225
00:34:53,925 --> 00:34:55,551
we can stay together forever.

226
00:34:56,052 --> 00:34:57,344
Really?

227
00:35:07,647 --> 00:35:10,149
May the Buddha bless you.

228
00:35:16,865 --> 00:35:20,326
Yangjin, wait for me.

229
00:35:22,996 --> 00:35:24,830
I'll wait for you.

230
00:35:53,735 --> 00:35:57,696
I can't go.
I can't get through. It's too cold.

231
00:35:59,949 --> 00:36:00,991
So cold.

232
00:36:08,541 --> 00:36:09,792
The path is too cold.

233
00:36:11,544 --> 00:36:12,836
Can't get anything through it.

234
00:36:28,520 --> 00:36:29,603
Where's your kid?

235
00:36:40,907 --> 00:36:41,907
I am sorry.

236
00:36:42,992 --> 00:36:44,076
Don't touch me.

237
00:36:44,953 --> 00:36:46,453
I'll bring bad luck to you.

238
00:37:07,308 --> 00:37:08,559
I know this is hard,

239
00:37:09,060 --> 00:37:13,856
but it's not going to be the last
hardship you are facing in your life.

240
00:37:25,994 --> 00:37:28,746
There, there.

241
00:37:31,875 --> 00:37:32,875
It's my mom.

242
00:37:34,627 --> 00:37:35,627
My mom.

243
00:37:38,131 --> 00:37:39,214
Mama!

244
00:37:40,592 --> 00:37:41,592
Mama.

245
00:37:44,137 --> 00:37:45,554
My mom loves me very much.

246
00:37:47,932 --> 00:37:50,184
When I signed up for the military
and went away to war,

247
00:37:53,354 --> 00:37:54,772
she was worried
that I was going to get killed.

248
00:37:57,984 --> 00:38:01,403
That's the sadness
that I never want my mom to feel.

249
00:38:03,448 --> 00:38:07,034
I'd imagine that your son in heaven...

250
00:38:08,077 --> 00:38:10,037
...wouldn't want you
to feel that either.

251
00:38:12,582 --> 00:38:14,500
This must be the fairy's clothes.

252
00:38:15,460 --> 00:38:16,710
It's so pretty.

253
00:38:28,807 --> 00:38:29,973
Her name is Lisa.

254
00:38:34,479 --> 00:38:36,480
My dad was a military man.

255
00:38:38,900 --> 00:38:41,276
I think when I joined the military too,

256
00:38:43,154 --> 00:38:45,823
it just gives her another
life to have to worry about.

257
00:38:51,746 --> 00:38:53,080
I am still alive.

258
00:40:04,569 --> 00:40:07,321
Big guy! Big guy!

259
00:40:08,114 --> 00:40:09,406
What are you doing here?

260
00:40:12,869 --> 00:40:15,078
This is how we greet
each other around here.

261
00:40:19,208 --> 00:40:22,461
Let's sit down. Please sit.

262
00:40:24,088 --> 00:40:27,841
I've got something tasty.
See, this is for you. Eat.

263
00:40:29,969 --> 00:40:31,720
Eat. Help yourself.

264
00:40:33,056 --> 00:40:34,306
It is delicious.

265
00:40:36,768 --> 00:40:37,935
